    "instruction": "Load metric.csv, parse timestamp as UTC datetimes. For each (cmdb_id,kpi_name) compute global P95 of value using the full series. Then filter metric records to the incident window: start=2024-01-23 06:50:39 UTC, end=2024-01-23 07:20:39 UTC (inclusive). For each (cmdb_id,kpi_name) within the incident window, count anomaly points where value >= global P95. For groups whose global P95==0, treat points with value>0 as anomalies. Produce a compact table of up to top 20 rows sorted by anomaly count descending with columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, anomaly_count, earliest_anomaly_timestamp (UTC), latest_anomaly_timestamp (UTC), max_value_in_window, global_p95, severity_ratio = max_value_in_window / global_p95 (use None or a large number if global_p95==0). Also return: total number of metric records in the incident window and number of distinct (cmdb_id,kpi_name) that had >=1 anomaly. Limit returned rows to top 20." 
