{
    "analysis": "Previous metric-level analysis found many persistent anomalies (value >= global P95) across infrastructure components — notably many 'socket' metrics on various mongo/mysql services and some 'mem' on mysql. However, the official root-cause component must be chosen from the provided candidate services (ts-auth-service, ts-order-service, ts-route-service, ts-train-service, ts-travel-service). The metric scan so far was broad and shows system-wide backend anomalies but did not specifically focus on these five candidate services. To localize the root cause we must now restrict metric analysis to only those five candidate services and see which of them (if any) have consecutive KPI anomalies inside the incident window. If multiple candidates show faults, we will then use traces to pick the most downstream faulty service within call chains.",
